'''Kim Seung-gyu''' ({{langx|ko|김승규}}; born 30 September 1990) is a South Korean professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for [[J1 League]] club [[FC Tokyo]] and the [[South Korea national football team|South Korea national team]].

==Club career==
Kim was a much-anticipated youth player of [[Ulsan Hyundai FC|Ulsan Hyundai]], and joined the senior team after graduating middle school. However, he usually played in reserve team and high school's team for a long time. He became Ulsan's main goalkeeper after showing impressive performances in important opportunities while existing goalkeeper [[Kim Young-kwang (footballer, born 1983)|Kim Young-kwang]] was injured in 2013. He was also selected for the [[K League Best XI]] in that season.<ref name="Awards">{{cite web |url=https://sports.news.naver.com/news.nhn?oid=001&aid=0006630126 |script-title=ko:<프로축구> 김신욱, K리그 클래식 MVP…감독상은 황선홍(종합) |website=[[Naver]] |publisher=[[Yonhap News Agency]] |language=ko |date=3 December 2013 |access-date=20 August 2021}}</ref>

When playing for [[Vissel Kobe]], Kim was selected as one of three outstanding [[J.League]] goalkeepers in the 2016 season, who were nominated for the [[J.League Best XI]], but lost to [[Shusaku Nishikawa]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.jleague.jp/news/article/7538/ |title=２０１６Ｊリーグ優秀選手賞 受賞選手が決定【Ｊリーグアウォーズ】 |publisher=J.League |language=ja |date=2016-11-18 |access-date=2023-08-15}}</ref>

Kim joined [[Saudi Pro League]] club [[Al Shabab FC (Riyadh)|Al-Shabab]] on 6 July 2022.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.football-asian.com/news/articleView.html?idxno=2311 |title=Kim Seung-Gyu officially joined Al Shabab |publisher=Football-Asian |date=2022-07-06 |access-date=2023-08-15}}</ref> He kept the third highest number of clean sheets with 11 clean sheets in the [[2022–23 Saudi Pro League]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.spl.sa/en/spl-statistics?seasonID=719a7123292aed3ad0abea46df4f4c9b&seasonNID=2022&stats_section=players_ranking |title=Statistics - 2022/2023 |publisher=Saudi Pro League |access-date=2023-08-15 |archive-date=15 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230815005726/https://www.spl.sa/en/spl-statistics?seasonID=719a7123292aed3ad0abea46df4f4c9b&seasonNID=2022&stats_section=players_ranking |url-status=dead }}</ref> He kept clean sheets in all four matches until the quarter-finals of the [[2023 Arab Club Champions Cup]], but conceded three goals in a semi-final defeat against [[Al Hilal SFC|Al-Hilal]].<ref name="GSA">{{cite web |url=https://globalsportsarchive.com/people/soccer/kim-seunggyu/11640/ |title=Kim Seunggyu - Matches |publisher=Global Sports Archive |access-date=2023-08-15}}</ref>

==International career==
=== 2014 World Cup ===
Kim made his senior international debut against [[Peru national football team|Peru]] on 14 August 2013 in a goalless draw, keeping a clean sheet in his debut.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.yna.co.kr/view/AKR20130814223000007 |script-title=ko:<한·페루축구> 정성룡 긴장시킨 새내기 골키퍼 김승규 |publisher=[[Yonhap News Agency]] |language=ko |date=14 August 2013 |access-date=18 July 2022}}</ref>

Kim was named in [[South Korea national football team|South Korea's squad]] for the [[2014 FIFA World Cup]] as the second-choice goalkeeper behind [[Jung Sung-ryong]]. He did not play the first two games, but after Jung's poor performance against [[Algeria national football team|Algeria]] he was selected to play against [[Belgium national football team|Belgium]]. He made numerous saves, but conceded one as Korea lost 1–0. Despite the loss, Kim was well praised by the fans for his performance, conceding only one goal against one of the top ranked teams in the world on his World Cup debut.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.donga.com/news/Sports/article/all/20140627/64723869/3 |script-title=ko:골키퍼 김승규, 벨기에전 눈부신 활약…“실점은 내실수” 눈물 |publisher=[[The Dong-a Ilbo]] |language=ko |date=27 June 2014 |access-date=18 July 2022}}</ref>

=== 2014 Asian Games ===
Kim was named as an over-aged player for the [[South Korea national under-23 football team|South Korean under-23 team]] to play in the [[Football at the 2014 Asian Games|2014 Asian Games]]. Kim helped his team get a gold medal for the first time in 28 years. Kim conceded no goals in the six matches he played and was granted a military exemption.<ref name="AsianGames">{{cite news |url=https://www.inews24.com/view/853401 |script-title=ko:[AG]'6경기 무실점' 김승규, 금메달의 마지막 버팀목 |publisher=JoyNews24 |language=ko |date=2 October 2014 |access-date=18 July 2022}}</ref>

Kim was selected for South Korea's squad for the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]] in Russia,<ref>{{cite web|title=Revealed: Every World Cup 2018 squad – 23-man & preliminary lists & when will they be announced?|url=https://www.goal.com/en-gb/news/revealed-every-world-cup-2018-squad-23-man-preliminary-lists/oa0atsduflsv1nsf6oqk576rb|website=Goal.com|access-date=18 May 2018}}</ref> but the manager [[Shin Tae-yong]] chose [[Jo Hyeon-woo]] as his main goalkeeper, and so he couldn't appear during the competition.

=== 2022 World Cup ===
After the 2018 World Cup, South Korea's next manager [[Paulo Bento]] had great faith in Kim. He participated in the [[2019 AFC Asian Cup]], conceding two goals during five matches until the quarter-finals. In the [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification (AFC)|2022 FIFA World Cup qualification]], he conceded only three goals during 14 appearances, helping South Korea qualify for the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.yna.co.kr/view/AKR20220202002800007 |script-title=ko:[AG]'6경기 무실점' 김승규, 금메달의 마지막 버팀목 |language=ko |publisher=[[Yonhap News Agency]] |date=2 February 2022 |access-date=18 July 2022}}</ref>

In [[2022 FIFA World Cup|2022]], Kim participated in the World Cup as the first-choice goalkeeper for the first time. During the group stage, he was criticised for failing to block any of [[Ghana national football team|Ghana]]'s three shots on target, but proved his abilities by conceding only one goal against [[Uruguay national football team|Uruguay]] and [[Portugal national football team|Portugal]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.seoul.co.kr/news/newsView.php?id=20221203500020 |script-title=ko:‘자동문’에서 ‘거미손’ 된 김승규 “가나·우루과이 전 기다릴 때 1초도 너무 길어”|publisher=[[Seoul Shinmun]] |language=ko |date=2022-12-03 |access-date=2023-01-15}}</ref> He met [[Brazil national football team|Brazilian]] forwards in the round of 16, and struggled to defend against them in a 4–1 defeat.

Kim was named in the national team for the [[2023 AFC Asian Cup]]. He played against [[Bahrain national football team|Bahrain]] in South Korea's first match, but was absent from the rest of the Asian Cup matches due to a cruciate ligament injury.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/2024-01-19/sports/football/Goalkeeper-Kim-Seunggyu-ruled-out-of-AFC-Asian-Cup-with-ACL-tear-/1962615 |title=Korea starting keeper Kim Seung-gyu ruled out of Asian Cup with ACL tear |website=[[Korea JoongAng Daily]] |date=2024-01-19 |access-date=2024-01-31}}</ref>

=== 2026 World Cup ===
On 16 May 2026, Kim was named in South Korea's squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/cwy29rxjg47o|title=South Korea captain Son picked for fourth World Cup|date=16 May 2026|access-date=16 May 2026|website=BBC Sport}}</ref>

==Style of play==
Known as one of the most versatile goalkeepers in South Korea, Kim is originally noted for his quick reflexes and movement, and also polished up his passing skills in the [[J1 League]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.footballist.co.kr/news/articleView.html?idxno=95102 |script-title=ko:[人사이드] ① 김승규의 골키퍼論 “공부하고 연구해야 막을 수 있다” |publisher=Footballist |language=ko |date=21 October 2016 |access-date=19 July 2022}}</ref>

